Media Release: Update on the coronavirus and vaccine rollout by Premier Alan Winde 4 March 2021 As of 1pm on 4 March, the Western Cape has 3254 active Covid-19 infections with a total of 275 878 confirmed Covid-19 cases and 261 384 recoveries. A total of 15 295 vaccines had been administered by 5pm on 3 March. Total confirmed COVID-19 cases 275 878 Total recoveries 261 384 Vaccines administered 15 295 Total deaths 11 240 Total active cases (currently infected patients) 3254 Tests conducted 1347009 Hospitalisations 1109 with 255 in ICU or highcare The Western Cape has recorded 18 additional deaths, bringing the total number of COVID-19 related deaths in the province to 11 240. We send our condolences to their loved ones at this time. Additional data is available on the Western Cape Covid-19 data dashboard which also features active cases per sub-district, active cases per 100 000 and 7-day moving averages. Access the data dashboard here: https://coronavirus.westerncape.gov.za/covid-19-dashboard Blue Dot taxi service launch: Earlier today, Minister of Transport and Public Works BonginkosiMadikizela and I attended the launch of the Blue Dot taxi service pilot. Read more about this innovative project which aims to make taxis safer for commuters here: https://www.westerncape.gov.za/news/premier-winde-and-minister-madikizela-launch-blue-dot-taxi-service-pilot-0#overlay-context=node/56196/draft. Issued by Western Cape Office of the Premier, 4 March 2021